The paper focuses on using machine learning algorithms to assist with literature reviews in the software engineering field, specifically in identifying test case prioritization techniques for automated UI testing. This falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves text mining and information retrieval (cs.IR), as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) in the form of the human-in-the-loop active learning text miner.
